wiki.content: Cool Girl is a song by Swedish recording artist Tove Lo. It was written by Tove with the record production duo The Struts, who also produced the track. "Cool Girl" was released on 4 August 2016 as the lead single from her second studio album, "Lady Wood." "Cool Girl" is a technopop song written by Tove Lo, Ludvig Söderberg, and Jakob Jerlström, with its production handled by the latter two as the production duo The Struts. Lyrically, the song is about an invitation to form a non-traditional and non-monogamous romance, in which the singer describes herself as a "cool girl" interested in an open relationship. According to Lo, the song's main lyrical theme was inspired by a scene from the feature film Gone Girl (2014), where the its titular character (portayed by Rosamund Pike) "goes from being a victim to a psycho."
